The markets' mood reversed Thursday after data showed that industrial orders in the euro zone rose 3.8% in May from the previous month.

PARAGRAPH.#text: Jim Cramer's been a big fan of Intuitive Surgical, and it's easy to understand why: The stock is his kind of stock. It's been going straight up, largely because the company, which makes a robotic surgical system, has been performing better than expectations. But as I noted on the TV show, there's the stock, and then there's the company -- and right now, it appears the stock's moved well ahead of the company. The fact that a stock is soaring doesn't mean a company will be a big winner.
